        "ratings": [
            {
                "comment": "I took a few years off between Spanish classes and was really worried about jumping back in. I had Deneille as my teacher, and she is amazing! First off, she remembered me from two years ago. She gave me extra help during office hours and spent a lot of time reteaching areas that I was struggling with. I would definitely recommend her to anyone! )",
                "difficulty_rating": 3,
                "quality_rating": 5
            },
            {
                "comment": "Was slightly worried about the transition from high school to college Spanish, as I heard many professors were reluctant to answer questions or provide clear expectations. Deneille made her expectations very clear and was able to help us a great amount. AWESOME at answering questions and providing more clarity on topics. Recommend her to everyone.",
                "difficulty_rating": 3,
                "quality_rating": 5
            },
            {
                "comment": "Great professor - personality and teaching. She's super easy to talk to, and going into her office hours helped a TON. However, sometimes she talked too fast and expected everyone to understand what she was saying, so it was difficult to know what was going on sometimes. Other than that, she's a pretty fair grader and relatively easy class.",
                "difficulty_rating": 2,
                "quality_rating": 4
            },
            {
                "comment": "I love Deneille. She is soo nice and helpful. She is such a sweetheart. She sends you books of review packets to help study and is always available if you need help. I've never had a Spanish professor/ta who was so clear.",
                "difficulty_rating": 3,
                "quality_rating": 5
            },
            {
                "comment": "She tries very hard to pay attention to what the class needs. If more time is needed for grammar or a story, then she'll adjust her plans to make sure everyone is more comfortable with the material. She speaks very clearly in Spanish, has a good sense of humor, and overall I really enjoyed her as my profe.",
                "difficulty_rating": 2,
                "quality_rating": 5
            },
            {
                "comment": "Profe was a very good spanish teacher that was good at explaining all the concepts.  Be prepared to speak all spanish in this class (obviously) but if you really don't understand something she will speak in English during her office hours (which she is very helpful during).  Studying is key in this class if you want to do well.",
                "difficulty_rating": 3,
                "quality_rating": 5
            },
            {
                "comment": "Very nice and good at explaining concepts, 204 isn't an easy class-lots of verb forms! Tests aren't too hard. Compared to my 203 TA, I feel treated a bit like a baby in this class.",
